{
  "stem": "2718.4",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 12.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We knew what we knew and, and, and we, we tried to, to stay sane.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And, and what kept us going also was we knew that my-- that my mother and my sister were alive when we left Auschwitz.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So one year after Muhldorf, we, we were-- we were put into barracks like any other camp.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I think the barracks were much the same in every camp.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I don't know how many people were in the barrack.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "In other camps, we had I think about 120 people to a barrack.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And there was a blockalteste, which was the block elder, and, and a couple of other people who performed the, the-- controlled the, the, the blocks so that everything went in a normal way.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And there was-- in the morning there was an appel and in the evening.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We were taken out to work every morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "We were marched out to a so-called [GERMAN], which was we were building huge, big hangars for airplanes for, for the Germans, airplane hangars.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean I, I don't know exactly the size of it, but they were big enough to, to house an airplane.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And that was-- we built it from, from reinforced concrete.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And part of the job was to-- as the-- as the railway trucks arrived, it was loaded with, with cement bags, which was 50 kilo each.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "To unload it, there was a team of approximately 16 people to each-- to each wagon.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And there were 250 bags of cement in every wagon.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So why I know it?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Because believe me, we counted every bag we unloaded.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We counted it many ti-- many times.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "So what, what the work was, two people stood-- we'd open the doors.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
